President Trump delivers remarks on the success of negotiations with Turkey regarding the situation in Syria. He expresses gratitude towards President Erdogan, Vice President Pence, and Secretary of State Pompeo for their efforts. The President highlights that this outcome, which involves a 22-mile strip and a five-day ceasefire, is a significant achievement that previous administrations were unable to accomplish. He emphasizes the importance of protecting lives and preventing further conflict. The President mentions that the Kurds are satisfied with the resolution and that ISIS will be under strict control. He also addresses the issue of sanctions, stating that they will not be necessary as Turkey is taking appropriate actions. The President commends President Erdogan for his leadership and praises the positive impact of the negotiated agreement on Turkey, the Kurds, and civilization as a whole.